on d c but this project never materialized and porter turned to patrick nesbitt edgar in january  to take over the project but edgar did not finish the work and by  the project was abandoned title page of the october  edition of american turf register edited by porter porter also served as an arbiter of disputes about sports rules and sports betting porter also encouraged new authors from the south and the west to write in his newspaper and helped them get books published he also edited two collections of short stories from the frontier the big bear of arkansas in  and a quarter race in kentucky and other sketches in  besides the sporting interests the spirit was involved in the emergence of american literature especially the tall tale form of humor porter encouraged southwestern authors to write and publish their short stories in the spirit and was involved in getting their works published in book form he was the editor for two of these collections the big bear of arkansas published in  and a quarter race in kentucky and other sketches published in  porter was instrumental in encouraging the career of johnson hooper another writer who contributed to the spirit was henry william herbert who wrote under the pen name frank forester the panic of  hurt the spirits circulation but porter responded by buying out his main competition the american turf register and sporting magazine and moved it to new york city porter edited the turf register until the paper stopped being published in  porter continued the publication of annual stallion lists and the publication of lists of horses owned by breeders however the purchase of the american turf register strained porters finances and he sold the spirit to another printer john richards who retained porter as editor the s were prosperous but in the s the magazine again encountered difficulties around  porter left richards paper and in  another printer george wilkes began a new sporting newspaper which he called porters spirit of the times and employed porter as editor later lifeedit in  porter served as secretary for the new york jockey club during the famous match race between the fillies fashion and peytona at the union course on may   although the spirit and the american turf register were known for their coverage of horse racing porters main sporting interest for himself was fishing porter never married and three of his brothers died before porter himself caught a cold and died of consumption on july   in his house in new york city he left unfinished a biography of his friend wiliam herbert the journalist and historian frank luther mott wrote that porter undoubtedly did much to give american sports a respectable standing citationsedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l dizikes porter william trotter american national biography online  a b c d harrison background of the american stud book pp â€“  mott history of american magazines p   a b c d mott history of american magazines pp â€“  robertson history of thoroughbred racing in america p   harrison background of the american stud book pp â€“  harrison background of the american stud book p   a b c staff july   death of william t porter new york times  robertson history of thoroughbred racing in america p  referencesedit dizikes john  porter william trotter fee required american national biography online oxford university press retrieved november  Â  harrison fairfax  the background of the american stud book richmond va old dominion press oclcÂ Â  mott frank luther  a history of american magazines â€“ cambridge ma harvard university press oclcÂ Â  robertson william h p  the history of thoroughbred racing in america new york bonanza books lccnÂ Â  staff july   death of william t porter new york times retrieved november   registration required helpÂ  further readingedit brinley francis  life of william t porter new york d appleton oclcÂ Â  currentgarcia eugene november  mr spirit and the big bear of arkansas american literature  jstorÂ  doiÂ  currentg